component.author: William Denniss <wdenniss@google.com>, Steven E Wright <stevewright@google.com>, Julien Bodet <julien.bodet92@gmail.com>
component.publisher: William Denniss <wdenniss@google.com>, Steven E Wright <stevewright@google.com>, Julien Bodet <julien.bodet92@gmail.com>
component.name: AppAuth
component.description:
AppAuth for iOS and macOS is a client SDK for communicating with [OAuth 2.0] (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749) and [OpenID Connect] (http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html) providers. It strives to directly map the requests and responses of those specifications, while following the idiomatic style of the implementation language. In addition to mapping the raw protocol flows, convenience methods are available to assist with common tasks like performing an action with fresh tokens.
It follows the OAuth 2.0 for Native Apps best current practice ([RFC 8252](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8252)).
